data.Name: Created
data.Description: The resource instance has been created, but ingestion has not yet started.

data.Name: Curating
data.Description: The curation process is in progress. E.g., a Document ingestion is going through the process of extracting artefact, collecting metadata needed, etc.

data.Name: Curated
data.Description: The curation process has completed.

data.Name: CREATED
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Created" with Name="Created" instead. The resource instance has been created, but ingestion has not yet started.

data.Name: CURATING
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Curating" with Name="Curating" instead. The curation process is in progress. E.g. A Document ingestion is going through the process of extracting artefact, collecting metadata needed, etc.

data.Name: CURATED
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Curated" with Name="Curated" instead. The curation process has completed.

data.Name: Loading
data.Description: When the ingestion process received a request to create a resource and loading is in progress. This lifecycle stage is applicable to all group-types.

data.Name: Ordered
data.Description: The content related to a work-product-component is unavailable for consumption but ordered. This status is applicable to a number scenarios like 1) content uploads for large datasets, 2) content replication via, e.g., from connected data sources, or 3) commercial transactions, where data delivery has not been completed.

data.Name: Received
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Completed" with Name="Completed" instead. After 'Received', the resource records are created and the content file is placed into storage. This lifecycle stage is applicable only to work-product-component group-type records.

data.Name: Completed
data.Description: When the ingestion process has completed successfully and any associated content is ready for consumption. This status is applicable to all group-type records.

data.Name: Optimized
data.Description: The content has been placed in optimized storage, i.e., in Domain Data Management Services (DDMS). This status is applicable to work-product-component group-type records.

data.Name: Rescinded
data.Description: DEPRECATED: This status is never documented because 'soft' deletes remove the record from the index which means that the  deleted record is no longer discoverable. Records removed with the purge operation will be removed completely, i.e., not discoverable. Previous definition: When a resource is logically deleted from the data platform.  This means that the data, metadata, and content (e.g. file(s) and/or DDMS content) should not be used.

data.Name: LOADING
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Loading" with Name="Loading" instead. When the ingestion process received a request to create a resource.

data.Name: RECIEVED
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Received" with Name="Received" instead. After RECEIVED, the resource records are created and the content file is placed into storage.

data.Name: ACCEPTED
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Completed" with Name="Completed" instead. When the ingestion process has completed successfully.

data.Name: RESCINDED
data.Description: DEPRECATED: Please use Code="Rescinded" with Name="Rescinded" instead. When a resource is logically deleted from the data platform.  This means that the data, metadata, and content file(s) should not be used.

data.Name: Public
data.Description: DEPRECATED: The value is not recognized by platform services. Please refer to the platform Security and Compliance Legal service managing the so-called legal tags, which contain a securityClassification property. Applies to information which the company or individual routinely makes available to customers and third parties.

data.Name: Private
data.Description: DEPRECATED: The value is not recognized by platform services. Please refer to the platform Security and Compliance Legal service managing the so-called legal tags, which contain a securityClassification property. Applies to information available to employees and authorized third parties (e.g. contractors, interns) as part of routine business. A security incident involving unauthorized access to private information will have a severity level of Serious or Major, depending on the financial or time-to-recover impact, but never less than Serious. Unlabeled Information Assets are considered private by default.

data.Name: Confidential
data.Description: DEPRECATED: The value is not recognized by platform services. Please refer to the platform Security and Compliance Legal service managing the so-called legal tags, which contain a securityClassification property. Applies to information which, if disclosed, would be prejudicial to the interests of the company or would cause serious damage to the interest of the company or its employees. A security incident involving unauthorized access to Confidential information will have a severity level of Major or Catastrophic, depending on the financial or time-to-recover impact, but never less than Major.

data.Name: Secret
data.Description: DEPRECATED: The value is not recognized by platform services. Please refer to the platform Security and Compliance Legal service managing the so-called legal tags, which contain a securityClassification property. Information is classified as Secret when it provides the company with a significant competitive edge, or shows specific business strategies and organizational directions, or is essential to the technical or financial success of a specific product or service. Unauthorized disclosure would cause serious damage to the interests of the company. The severity of an information security incident involving unauthorized access to Secret information will be reported as Catastrophic or Multi-Catastrophic, depending on the financial or time-to-recover impact, but never less than Catastrophic.

data.Name: International Commission on Stratigraphy
data.Description: The International Commission on Stratigraphy (ICS) is the largest and oldest constituent scientific body in the International Union of Geological Sciences (IUGS). Its primary objective is to define precisely global units (systems, series and stages) of the International Chronostratigraphic Chart that, in turn, are the basis for the units (periods, epochs and age) of the International Geological Time Scale; thus setting global standards for the fundamental scale for expressing the history of the Earth.

data.Name: International Association of Drilling Contractors
data.Description: IADC (International Association of Drilling Contractors) is a non-profit trade association that is the global leader in advancing the drilling industry. IADC is recognized worldwide for their accreditation programs, conferences, advocacy efforts, and industry news.

data.Name: Certified
data.Description: A record can be used with high confidence for general business use, and it has undergone extensive quality verification to have met or exceeded defined business requirements. Confirmation may be associated with an auditable business process.

data.Name: Trusted
data.Description: A record can be used with high confidence for general business use due to its high level of known quality.

data.Name: Suitable
data.Description: A record has been deemed acceptable for general business use due to its adequate level of known quality even though it may contain minor quality issues. Use does not pose a significant business risk.

data.Name: Unsuitable
data.Description: A  record has been deemed unacceptable for general business use due to known or assumed quality issues. Use can pose a business risk.

data.Name: Unevaluated
data.Description: A record's quality and suitability for business use has not been assessed by a data quality process or otherwise assumed. "Unevaluated" is used as the "absent value" for TechnicalAssurance.

data.Name: Regulatory Identifier

data.Name: Unique Identifier

data.Name: Project Number

data.Name: Wellbore Number

data.Name: EDS Connected Source Identifier
data.Description: The alias type used when tagging an object in the receiver system instance with the identifier of the corresponding record in the connected, external source system. It is used while ingesting the data into receiver instance to capture associated parent records in the external source and receiver instance.

data.Name: Integer Code
data.Description: An alternative unique identifier code as integer number. Alias names are always strings, in this case the integer number is represented as string and is expected to be convertible to an integer number.
